This paper proposes a generative model using an Auto-encoder and normalizing flow, which is a popular approach in the field of machine learning for generative modeling. The paper focuses on comparing their model with related techniques and evaluating its performance on commonly used datasets. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the relationship between their model and its stochastic counterpart, which suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the sample quality of their model, which could be relevant to cs.SD (Sound).
